### SimpleMDB API Test – REST Client (VS Code)
### Base URL
@host = http://localhost:3000
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api/v1/movies
@movieID = 1

### -------------------------------------------------
### CREATE (POST) a new movie
### -------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": -1,
  "title": "Inception",
  "year": 2010,
  "description": "A thief enters dreams to steal secrets."
}

### -------------------------------------------------
### READ (GET) a single movie by ID
### -------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{movieID}}
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------------
### UPDATE (PUT) an existing movie by ID
### -------------------------------------------------
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{movieID}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Inception (Updated)",
  "year": 2010,
  "description": "A thief enters dreams to steal secrets (updated)."
}

### -------------------------------------------------
### DELETE (DELETE) a movie by ID
### -------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{movieID}}
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------------
### LIST (GET) movies with pagination
### -------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=1&size=10
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------------
### Additional tests: List page 2
### -------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=2&size=10
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------------
### Additional tests: Create with missing field (error case)
### -------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": -1,
  "title": "",
  "year": 2025
}

### -------------------------------------------------
### Additional tests: Read non-existent movie (404 case)
### -------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/9999
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------------
### Additional tests: Update non-existent movie (error case)
### -------------------------------------------------
PUT {{baseUrl}}/9999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Ghost Movie",
  "year": 2025,
  "description": "This movie does not exist."
}

### -------------------------------------------------
### Additional tests: Delete non-existent movie (idempotent)
### -------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/9999
Accept: application/json
